50|$|Primas {{was raised}} in Camden, New Jersey {{as a member of}} one of the city's most {{prominent}} families. He earned a bachelor's degree from Howard University in Washington, D.C., in 1971. Primas then joined <b>the</b> <b>Black</b> <b>People's</b> Unity Movement when he returned to Camden. Before becoming mayor, Primas was the Vice President of Burger King Entities, an economic-development program sponsored by <b>the</b> <b>Black</b> <b>People's</b> Unity Movement.|$|R
