50|$|In 2017, the '13 Dead, Nothing Said' {{exhibition}} was hosted at Goldsmiths College, University of London. The exhibition presents {{a body of}} photographs taken by Vron Ware documenting <b>the</b> <b>Black</b> <b>People’s</b> Day of Action on 2 March 1981. The images bear witness to an historic moment of community organising and resistance in post-war Britain.|$|R
